{"key":"processedPost-16719485","value":{"id":16719485,"first":16718870,"last":16720501,"when":1345301174,"utime":"08/18/12 05:46 PM","content":"I wouldn't.<br />The plugs have been inoculated from grain spawn.&nbsp; Taking them back to grain spawn is an extra vector of contamination as well beginning a new culture already possibly ravaged by senescence.&nbsp; Use plugs to inoculate logs, and use cultures to inoculate grain spawn.<br />To the original poster, oyster mushrooms like to fruit in 40F to 60F temperature with lots of rain and high humidity.&nbsp; It will take a month or two to get your spawn expanded and into your bulk substrates, depending on the procedures used.&nbsp; Adjust your procedure so it's time to fruit when your local weather meets the conditions described above.<br />RR","title":"Re: When should I start?"}}